#. type: Plain text
#: original_texis/msdos.texi:35
msgid "The behavior of Emacs on MS-Windows is reasonably similar to what is documented in the rest of the manual, including support for long file names, multiple frames, scroll bars, mouse menus, and subprocesses.  However, a few special considerations apply, and they are described here."
